      <title>Re: point of don factions?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=71315#M71315</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I think the idea is sound for the factions, but the large amount of work required to enable some to continue the storyline and progression is grossly unjust. It is obvious that many people have to do so much more than others based on a character choice they made years ago.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;While I personally am&amp;nbsp; not against the idea of having to do a bit more work than others, it remains that there are many who are. Therefore, rather than post just a negative message I have a couple suggestions.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1) There are tons of tasks that came out with OoW. It makes sense for people to raise factions for either DR or KoN from these. I have done a number of these and never get any meaningful faction adjustments.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;2) If a person chose an evil character/deity there should be tasks &lt;STRONG&gt;and&lt;/STRONG&gt; quests in their starting city (makes sense) that will allow them to increase the faction for Dark Reign. (this also applies to good races/deities) *** note *** BUT make them meaningful. If it takes 1500 faction points to get the the next faction level, doing a task or quest should equal more than 2 faction points&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;3) Add tasks that can be done solo. Some classes are always screwed whenever new things are introduced into the game.... see the post form the lvl 70 monk above.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;4) Add tasks that require you to combine (example) 100 spider silks and when you turn them in you get faction adjustments. These turned-in combines are then on the NPC for other players to purchase. This will tie in for tradeskillers and allow them another avenue for obtaining tradeskill drops/or combines they would not usually be able to get on their own.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Just a few ideas. Perhaps others have more.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
