    <item>
      <title>Re: point of don factions?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=71272#M71272</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;There were a number of good steps made to mitigate the effects of seperating the factions with DoN, but for me in the end it was wasted effort - the word I used was quite specific - the factions are "separate" not "meaningful". Having two routes to exactly the same thing doesnt increase your options, and due to the grouping nature of the game it actually reduces them in many cases.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Velious factions can act as almost the opposite of DoN faction - both can be seen to be fairly balanced, but in SoV their were different but roughly equal rewards to each faction decision - for dwarves you could get lower stat but faster/easier&amp;nbsp;to gain armour, and for kael/ss you had roughly equal difficulty, and similar level equipment but with different stats that certain classes might prefer other the opposite set. With the main named there were again various different drops but all balanced to their difficulty.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;If killing King Tormax and Yelinak and Dain gave exactly the same items, and&amp;nbsp;all sets of armour were farmed from exactly the same mobs to give exactly the same stats I dont think Velious would be as well remembered as it is today.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Thats not to say DoN was a failure, overall I like it - the rewards are decent and in line with effort for the majority of people, it feels like a grind a lot less than LDoN was, and the mission system is well set up and miles ahead of the LDoN tasks in terms of keeping things interesting. It also has a good mix of group/raid content compared to the raids of LDoN. But for me the faction is easily the biggest mistake in the expansion, there really is no purpose to it except as a failed attempt to put factions back in the game.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
